An arrest for suspicion of driving under the influence will not affect the playing status of San Diego Chargers wide receiver Vincent Jackson for Sunday's divisional playoff game at Pittsburgh.
Jackson was arrested on the DUI charge early Tuesday morning by the California Highway Patrol.
However, the fourth-year wide receiver likely will not face disciplinary action until the 2009 season.
