Along with the misdemeanor DUI allegation, California Highway Patrol Officer Brad Baehr said Jackson was cited for driving on probation for a prior DUI.
Jackson issued a statement released through the team.
``I was stopped by an officer,'' he said.
``I don't think any charges will be filed as a result of the stop.
In the event they are, I look forward to clearing my name and proving my innocence.''
Baehr said he was not aware of the particulars of the previous DUI charge and that results of Jackson's blood test are pending.
Jackson had his finest season in 2008 with with 59 receptions for 1,098 yards and seven touchdowns for the AFC West champions.
